item.title: Difference between "is" and "==" in Python
item.description: Python interview questions Definition and features of comparison operators operator “==” for value equality. It’s used to know if two objects have the same value. operator “is” for reference equality. It’s used to know if two references refer (or point) to the same object, i.e if they’re identical. Two objects are identical if they have the same memory address. Two objects having equal values are not necessarily identical.
